---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">About</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    Pantagruel Research is an independent research initiative at the intersection of
    <b>quantitative finance</b>, <b>machine learning</b> and <b>data science</b>.
    Our work focuses on the rigorous application of statistical models and modern AI techniques
    to problems in asset management, derivatives, risk and algorithmic trading —
    with a strong emphasis on mathematical foundations and production-ready implementations.
  </div>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────── CONTRIBUTOR 1 ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-5">
    <img
      src="/pantagruel-research/alejandro_prendes.jpeg"
      alt="Alejandro Prendes Cabo"
      class="w-24 h-24 rounded-full object-cover ring-2 ring-primary shrink-0"
    />
    <div>
      <div class="text-2xl font-bold">Alejandro Prendes Cabo</div>
      <div class="text-base opacity-70">Mathematician & AI Researcher · QUANT AI Lab</div>
      <a
        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alejandro-prendes-cabo/"
        target="_blank"
        class="text-sm link link-primary"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        LinkedIn ↗
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-8 text-justify">
    Mathematician and physicist specialized in artificial intelligence, with deep expertise in
    deep learning, MLOps and applied AI systems. At QUANT AI Lab he leads research on
    AI-powered quantitative strategies and contributes to open-source tooling for financial
    data science. Regular speaker at international AI and technology conferences and host of
    the <b>WallStreetWolverine</b> podcast on AI and quantitative finance.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-8">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Double Degree in Mathematics & Physics"
      subtitle="2012 to 2018 at Universidad de Oviedo, Oviedo, Spain"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-8">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="AI Researcher"
      subtitle="From 2021 to Present at QUANT AI Lab, Madrid, Spain"
    >
      Research and development of AI systems applied to quantitative finance and cybersecurity.
      Design of machine learning pipelines, deep learning architectures and MLOps infrastructure
      for production-grade deployments.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Co-founder & Quantitative Researcher"
      subtitle="From 2023 to Present at Pantagruel Research"
    >
      Independent research on the application of transformer models, reinforcement learning
      and probabilistic methods to financial time series forecasting, portfolio optimisation
      and algorithmic trading.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-8 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      <a href="https://coursera.org/verify/HURY47QNTUP6" target="_blank">
        MLOps: Machine Learning in Production – Coursera / DeepLearning.AI (2021)
      </a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="http://coursera.org/verify/USRR47YT4VW2" target="_blank">
        Convolutional Neural Networks – Coursera / DeepLearning.AI (2020)
      </a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.coursera.org/account/accomplishments/certificate/AXHY9J4J9N6S" target="_blank">
        Improving Deep Neural Networks – Coursera / DeepLearning.AI (2020)
      </a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="http://coursera.org/verify/A8MGU7E9LLDM" target="_blank">
        Neural Networks and Deep Learning – Coursera / DeepLearning.AI (2020)
      </a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2 mx-6 mb-12">
    <li>Python</li>
    <li>PyTorch</li>
    <li>TensorFlow</li>
    <li>scikit-learn</li>
    <li>Pandas / NumPy</li>
    <li>Deep Learning</li>
    <li>MLOps</li>
    <li>Time Series</li>
    <li>NLP / LLMs</li>
    <li>Docker / Cloud</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────── CONTRIBUTOR 2 ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="mb-4 flex items-center gap-5 mt-4">
    <img
      src="/pantagruel-research/javier_fernandez.jpeg"
      alt="Javier Fernández Sánchez de la Viña"
      class="w-24 h-24 rounded-full object-cover ring-2 ring-primary shrink-0"
    />
    <div>
      <div class="text-2xl font-bold">Javier Fernández Sánchez de la Viña</div>
      <div class="text-base opacity-70">Quant Trader · CFA · University Lecturer</div>
      <a
        href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/javier-fernandez-sanchez-de-la-vina-8082bb176/"
        target="_blank"
        class="text-sm link link-primary"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        LinkedIn ↗
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-8 text-justify">
    Physicist, mathematician and economist with over five years of experience as a derivatives
    trader, specialising in volatility strategies and structured products. CFA charterholder.
    Currently combines active quantitative research with university teaching at
    <b>CUNEF Universidad</b>, <b>Universidad de las Hespérides</b> and <b>UNIE Universidad</b>,
    covering Financial Markets, Derivatives, Risk, Portfolio Construction and Macroeconomics.
    Previously a quantitative trader at <b>Arfima Trading</b> and a guest lecturer on the
    <em>Máster en Finanzas Cuantitativas y Métodos Computacionales</em> at Afi Escuela.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-8">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Physics, Mathematics & Economics"
      subtitle="Oriel College, University of Oxford, Oxford, United Kingdom"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-8">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="University Lecturer – Financial Markets & Quantitative Finance"
      subtitle="From 2025 to Present at CUNEF Universidad · Universidad de las Hespérides · UNIE Universidad, Madrid, Spain"
    >
      Teaching across multiple institutions: Derivatives, Risk Management, Portfolio Construction,
      Quantitative Finance and Macroeconomics. Guest lecturer on the Máster en Finanzas
      Cuantitativas y Métodos Computacionales at Afi Escuela.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Quant Trader – Derivatives & Volatility"
      subtitle="From 2018 to 2024 at Arfima Trading, Madrid, Spain"
    >
      Over five years trading derivatives with a focus on volatility strategies and structured
      products. Development of quantitative models for pricing, hedging and systematic
      execution across equity and fixed-income options markets.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Co-founder & Quantitative Researcher"
      subtitle="From 2023 to Present at Pantagruel Research"
    >
      Research on volatility modelling, derivatives pricing, factor-based portfolio construction
      and the application of machine learning to financial markets. Author of in-depth technical
      articles combining academic rigour with practical implementation.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-8 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.cfainstitute.org/" target="_blank">CFA Charterholder – CFA Institute</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2 mx-6 mb-10">
    <li>Python</li>
    <li>R</li>
    <li>Derivatives Pricing</li>
    <li>Volatility Models</li>
    <li>Portfolio Opt.</li>
    <li>Risk Management</li>
    <li>Factor Models</li>
    <li>Econometrics</li>
    <li>Structured Products</li>
    <li>Macro Finance</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
